---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About | Full Product Dev"
  description="Learn about our mission to help teams build better products through engineering excellence and user-centered design."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="article-content" style="max-width: 65ch; margin: 0 auto;">
      <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h1>About Full Product Dev</h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Building better products through engineering excellence
        </p>
      </header>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>Our Story</h2>
        <p>
          Full Product Dev was born from a simple observation: the best products come from teams 
          that seamlessly blend product thinking with engineering excellence. Too often, these 
          disciplines work in silos, leading to products that are either technically impressive 
          but miss the mark with users, or user-friendly but built on shaky technical foundations.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          We believe there's a better way. By "shifting product focus left" - integrating 
          product thinking into every stage of the development process - teams can build 
          software that not only solves real problems but does so in a scalable, maintainable way.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Product Strategy</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Understanding user needs, defining requirements, and building roadmaps that drive real impact.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Engineering Excellence</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Best practices for writing clean, scalable code that stands the test of time.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">User Experience</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Designing interfaces and interactions that users love and understand intuitively.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Team Collaboration</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Building bridges between product, design, and engineering for more effective collaboration.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>Our Approach</h2>
        <p>
          We believe in learning by doing. Every article includes practical examples, 
          real-world case studies, and actionable advice you can apply immediately. 
          We're not here to preach theory - we're here to share what actually works 
          in the trenches of product development.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Our Core Values:</h3>
        <ul style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <li><strong>User-first thinking</strong> - Every technical decision should consider the user impact</li>
          <li><strong>Continuous learning</strong> - The best teams are always iterating and improving</li>
          <li><strong>Quality over quantity</strong> - Better to build one great feature than ten mediocre ones</li>
          <li><strong>Cross-functional collaboration</strong> - Great products require great teamwork</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-50) 0%, var(--bg-secondary) 100%); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Join Our Community</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Ready to build better products? Start by exploring our latest articles 
          and join the conversation about the future of product development.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog" class="hero-cta">
          Read Our Articles
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
